{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Instead of using the traditional centralized datasets that LLMs are provided with, developing LLMs on blockchains enables the creation of decentralized datasets.",
    "These datasets are less likely to be tampered with and can be easily audited for accuracy.",
    "Gong et al. [37] present the DLLM to evolve after the training process.",
    "This was implemented by adjusting neural network parameters, enabling the LLM to continue learning during its use.",
    "Additionally, blockchain-based systems can help assess where data poisoning may occur, and as shown in [55], blockchain can protect datasets and detect potential inference attacks through a two-level privacy preserving module."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
